The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing a 3D human face from a single in-the-wild color image using a novel model-based deep convolutional autoencoder. This work involves computer vision, machine learning, and graphics, which are all subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which are covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the use of expert-designed generative models, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves graphics, which is covered in cs.GR (Computer Graphics), and the use of monocular images, which is covered in cs.MM (Multimedia).
